The paper deals with the problem of computing minimal absent words in a collection of words, which is a problem in string algorithms and data structures. This suggests that the paper belongs to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also mentions applications in data compression and bioinformatics, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. The use of text indexing and output-sensitive space further suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the focus on combinatorial objects such as words and factors suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category.
